&nbsp;
In front of the audience of the magistrates it tries to be reassuring and defines "dogma" and "non-negotiable" the principle of independence of the magistrates, > judging and demanding". The theme of separation of careers and functions and composition of Csm remains: "We have been commissioned by the electoral body to reform justice and will land on the Bordeaux Convention." Responding to a magistrate then guaranteed that in the composition of the new Csm, "the prevalence of togate magistrates will be absolute". It also opens on reforms, because it is not true that "things have been written and that they are irrevocably decided. I hope that there is no more talk of conflict between politics and judiciary, but of open and open dialogue, of opposite ideas, even of proposals from you."
&nbsp;
The Anm is not there: "Nordio once again reassured us about the intention of maintaining the autonomy and independence of the judiciary. But it confirmed once again - short cuts the vice president of the National Association magistrates Alessandra Maddalena - the intention to move forward with the reform on the separation of careers, which once again, we repeat, is incompatible with the maintenance of autonomy and independence of the judiciary. So we continue to reiterate our opposition to a reform that distorts the constitutional system to the detriment of citizens." On the need to keep a comparison channel active, he insisted the vice president of the Csm, Fabio Pinelli: "It is necessary that institutions dialogue, that dialogue judiciary and politics. And the theme of impartiality and interpretation can be a map of tornasoles to measure the capacity of dialogue between politics and judiciary." There is also room for parties. "How anticipated on reforms, beginning with the separation of careers, sees our firm opposition," says the leader of the PD, Elly Schlein, > talking about "increasing insufficiency by the government towards the balance of powers, the current institutional structure and towards the same judiciary on which a muscular and aggressive attitude flows. It is necessary to hear the voice of the judiciary, rather than to feed a dangerous institutional clash that does not suit the country".
&nbsp;
Matteo Renzi > does not believe that the reform will go to port: "I'm embarrassed by the way the government operates. Advertisements instead of reforms and exchange Twitter for Official Journal and after two years - the leader of Italy alive - did not bring home even a reform. The text does not exist." Yet, for the former prime minister, "there is a need for constitutional reform, but this government of gossip cannot do it." &nbsp;&nbsp;

