AGI -&nbsp;<span> "For me it was a moment of great emotion to embrace Father Maurizio Patriciello that I judge to be a hero of our time. He is a man who daily dedicates his life to others, to the weakest, to young people and to those who live in degradation. As far as I can be, I will always be close to him.” &nbsp;</span><span> The Minister of Culture, Gennaro Sangiuliano, said that in today's afternoon he went personally to Caivano, in the parish of the Green Park, to express solidarity to Father Maurizio Patriciello, and also met the many faithful and young people who collaborate with the priest.</span>
The visit of the Minister of Culture follows the controversy that involves the anti-Camorra priest who had been appellated in a derogatory way as "Pippo Baudo of the northern area of Naples" by the president of the Campania region, Vincenzo De Luca. An externation that in addition to provoking the reaction of the priest who has remembered to live for over two years under escort, triggered a wave of solidarity bi-partisan.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"'Pippo Baudo in the north of Naples'. Thus, derided, the president of the Campania Region defines Fr Maurizio Patriciello, a priest, a man who tries to fight the chamorra and give answers to the Persian families where those like De Luca failed to do so, or did not want to do so". So the president of the Girogia Meloni Social Council. "Father Maurizio lives under guard because he has become a goal of chamorists who do not like his tenacity to remove young people from drugs and crime. Instead of helping Father Maurizio, making him feel the support of the institutions, De Luca laughs at him, and so he makes a scary signal," he adds. "I want to tell Father Maurizio that the State is at his side. Which is not alone. And that men and women who have not exchanged institutions for the stage of a cabaret, but carry out their task with discipline and honor, know and recognize the value of his sacrifices", he concludes under the hashtag 'I am Father Maurizio'.

